President Bush has named Appeals Court Judge Clarence Thomas for the
Supreme Court.  Thomas has served as Equal Employment Opportunity
Commission Chairman and is known for his opposition to affirmative
action and many government programs.  Thomas was raised by
grandparents in Georgia and credits them with his achievements.</SUM>
